Dr. Jill Biden, the wife of former Vice President Joe Biden, will be delivering two commencement addresses this spring. The first will be at Broward College in Fort Lauderdale, Florida, on May 4. Broward College is the largest institution of higher education in Broward County, with over 66,000 students. The second address will be at Southwestern Community College in Creston, Iowa, on May 11. Southwestern Community College is a comprehensive two-year public institution that offers various programs and serves approximately 1,750 credit students and 9,000 non-credit students. Dr. Biden, who has been an educator for over 30 years, will be sharing her insights and experiences with the graduates.